docs/content/docs/guides/plugin-development.mdx lines 312-316 show:
```typescript
const created = await postJSON(
  '/api/items',
  { title: 'New item' },
  itemSchema,
);
```

The actual postJSON signature is `postJSON(url, body, init?, schema?)` — the schema is the 4th argument, not 3rd. See platform/plugin-sdk/src/fetch.ts lines 142-176 (PostJSON interface and implementation). Passing a Zod schema as the 3rd arg would be silently interpreted as FetchFromPageOptions, and no validation would occur.

Correct example:
```typescript
const created = await postJSON(
  '/api/items',
  { title: 'New item' },
  undefined,
  itemSchema,
);
```

Also check if there's an explanatory paragraph around line 300-310 that describes the schema parameter — update it to mention the 4-arg signature.

docs/content/docs/guides/resources-prompts.mdx lines 490-503 show:
```typescript
export default class TrackerPlugin extends OpenTabsPlugin {
  // ... fields ...
}
```

The build command (platform/plugin-tools/src/commands/build.ts lines 950-953) expects mod.default to be an INSTANCE, not a class:
```typescript
const mod = (await import(...)) as { default?: OpenTabsPlugin };
const defaultExport = mod.default;
if (!defaultExport) {
  throw new Error('Plugin module must export a default instance of OpenTabsPlugin.');
}
```

Exporting the class would fail because class properties (name, version, etc.) aren't available on the constructor.

Fix: Change to `export default new TrackerPlugin()` (matching the pattern shown earlier in plugin-development.mdx line 84).

Two issues:

1. docs/content/docs/guides/resources-prompts.mdx lines 480-488: createItem tool uses `fetchJSON('/api/items', { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify(params) })`. This won't set Content-Type: application/json (fetchFromPage only sets credentials: 'include'). Use postJSON instead:
```typescript
const item = await postJSON<{ id: string; title: string; url: string }>(
  '/api/items',
  params,
);
```
See platform/plugin-sdk/src/fetch.ts line 171 where postJSON sets Content-Type.

2. docs/content/docs/guides/error-handling.mdx line 387: Says 'The notFound factory also accepts a custom code' implying this is special to notFound. But ALL factory methods accept optional custom codes: auth(msg, code?), validation(msg, code?), timeout(msg, code?), internal(msg, code?). See platform/plugin-sdk/src/errors.ts lines 41-68. Reword to make clear that all factories support custom codes.
